{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015XsmhPLvHG1phpFUvPuN78","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Integration test for step2.py -- K_Step2 pressure, viscosity, XSPH kernel.\n     2→\n     3→Acceptance criteria:\n     4→  - Tait EOS: p_raw = k * (pow(rho/rho0, gamma) - 1); GRANULAR clamps >= 0,\n     5→    FLUID clamps >= -0.5*k, GAS uses linear k * max(rho - rho0, 0)\n     6→  - Pressure force: pressure_precalc * m_j * (p_i/rho_i^2 + p_j/rho_j^2) * grad_spiky_variable\n     7→  - Viscosity force: viscosity_precalc * m_j * (v_j - v_i) / rho_j * lap_visc_variable\n     8→  - XSPH (FLUID only): epsilon * sum(m_j / rho_avg * (v_j - v_i) * W_poly6)\n     9→  - STATIC (behavior_class == 3) -> zero force (early return)\n    10→  - SLEEPING (IS_SLEEPING flag) -> zero force (early return)\n    11→  - sph_force as float4 to sorted buffer; veleval_xsph to sorted veleval buffer\n    12→  - Two fluid particles at rest density -> ~zero net force\n    13→  - Compressed fluid particles -> repulsive forces (pushed apart)\n    14→  - Block size = 128, runs for 500K particles\n    15→\n    16→Requirements: cupy, numpy, an NVIDIA GPU with CUDA 12.x.\n    17→\"\"\"\n    18→\n    19→from __future__ import annotations\n    20→\n    21→import math\n    22→import os\n    23→import sys\n    24→\n    25→sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(__file__))\n    26→\n    27→import cupy\n    28→import numpy as np\n    29→\n    30→from hash_sort import (\n    31→    NUM_CELLS,\n    32→    build_grid_params,\n    33→    upload_grid_params as upload_hash_grid_params,\n    34→)\n    35→from step1 import (\n    36→    build_precalc_params,\n    37→    build_sim_params,\n    38→    upload_grid_params as upload_step1_grid_params,\n    39→    upload_precalc_params as upload_step1_precalc,\n    40→    upload_sim_params,\n    41→)\n    42→from step2 import (\n    43→    BLOCK_SIZE,\n    44→    GRANULAR_PARAMS_DTYPE,\n    45→    build_granular_params,\n    46→    compute_step2,\n    47→    get_module,\n    48→    upload_granular_params,\n    49→    upload_grid_params as upload_step2_grid_params,\n    50→    upload_materials,\n    51→    upload_precalc_params as upload_step2_precalc,\n    52→    upload_sim_params as upload_step2_sim,\n    53→)\n    54→from materials import (\n    55→    FLUID,\n    56→    GRANULAR,\n    57→    GAS,\n    58→    STATIC,\n    59→    MATERIALS,\n    60→    MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE,\n    61→    MAX_MATERIALS,\n    62→    build_material_array,\n    63→)\n    64→\n    65→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    66→# Constants matching acceptance criteria\n    67→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    68→\n    69→H = 0.04\n    70→H_SQ = H * H\n    71→SPACING = 0.02\n    72→RHO0 = 1000.0\n    73→MASS = RHO0 * SPACING**3  # 0.008 kg\n    74→VISCOSITY = 3.5\n    75→POLY6_COEFF = 315.0 / (64.0 * math.pi * H**9)\n    76→PRESSURE_PRECALC = 45.0 / (math.pi * H**6)\n    77→VISCOSITY_PRECALC = VISCOSITY * 45.0 / (math.pi * H**6)\n    78→\n    79→# packed_info helpers (mirror common.cuh macros)\n    80→def MAKE_PACKED(mat_id: int, behavior: int) -> int:\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4866d367-d48b-4a34-81f5-869c2bcf590b","uuid":"bbc941bf-257a-411a-9aa2-2c664d9c5721","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/test_step2.py","content":"\"\"\"Integration test for step2.py -- K_Step2 pressure, viscosity, XSPH kernel.\n\nAcceptance criteria:\n  - Tait EOS: p_raw = k * (pow(rho/rho0, gamma) - 1); GRANULAR clamps >= 0,\n    FLUID clamps >= -0.5*k, GAS uses linear k * max(rho - rho0, 0)\n  - Pressure force: pressure_precalc * m_j * (p_i/rho_i^2 + p_j/rho_j^2) * grad_spiky_variable\n  - Viscosity force: viscosity_precalc * m_j * (v_j - v_i) / rho_j * lap_visc_variable\n  - XSPH (FLUID only): epsilon * sum(m_j / rho_avg * (v_j - v_i) * W_poly6)\n  - STATIC (behavior_class == 3) -> zero force (early return)\n  - SLEEPING (IS_SLEEPING flag) -> zero force (early return)\n  - sph_force as float4 to sorted buffer; veleval_xsph to sorted veleval buffer\n  - Two fluid particles at rest density -> ~zero net force\n  - Compressed fluid particles -> repulsive forces (pushed apart)\n  - Block size = 128, runs for 500K particles\n\nRequirements: cupy, numpy, an NVIDIA GPU with CUDA 12.x.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport math\nimport os\nimport sys\n\nsys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(__file__))\n\nimport cupy\nimport numpy as np\n\nfrom hash_sort import (\n    NUM_CELLS,\n    build_grid_params,\n    upload_grid_params as upload_hash_grid_params,\n)\nfrom step1 import (\n    build_precalc_params,\n    build_sim_params,\n    upload_grid_params as upload_step1_grid_params,\n    upload_precalc_params as upload_step1_precalc,\n    upload_sim_params,\n)\nfrom step2 import (\n    BLOCK_SIZE,\n    GRANULAR_PARAMS_DTYPE,\n    build_granular_params,\n    compute_step2,\n    get_module,\n    upload_granular_params,\n    upload_grid_params as upload_step2_grid_params,\n    upload_materials,\n    upload_precalc_params as upload_step2_precalc,\n    upload_sim_params as upload_step2_sim,\n)\nfrom materials import (\n    FLUID,\n    GRANULAR,\n    GAS,\n    STATIC,\n    MATERIALS,\n    MATERIAL_PROPS_DTYPE,\n    MAX_MATERIALS,\n    build_material_array,\n)\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Constants matching acceptance criteria\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nH = 0.04\nH_SQ = H * H\nSPACING = 0.02\nRHO0 = 1000.0\nMASS = RHO0 * SPACING**3  # 0.008 kg\nVISCOSITY = 3.5\nPOLY6_COEFF = 315.0 / (64.0 * math.pi * H**9)\nPRESSURE_PRECALC = 45.0 / (math.pi * H**6)\nVISCOSITY_PRECALC = VISCOSITY * 45.0 / (math.pi * H**6)\n\n# packed_info helpers (mirror common.cuh macros)\ndef MAKE_PACKED(mat_id: int, behavior: int) -> int:","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":836}}}
