{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016unQSiTpB7RFJTwMidP6DW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The XSPH position update logic looks correct: `vel_new + (veleval_xsph - vel)` where `veleval_xsph - vel = eps * xsph_sum`. The acceptance criteria says \"pos_new = pos + dt * (vel_new + veleval_xsph)\" which I interpret as the `veleval_xsph` being the XSPH correction term (not the full velocity), but looking more carefully at the exact wording, it says \"veleval_xsph\" which from Step2 is the full velocity with XSPH blended. So the formula `pos + dt * (vel_new + veleval_xsph)` if taken literally would double-count. My interpretation is correct: use `vel_new + xsph_correction` where `xsph_correction = veleval_xsph - vel_old`.\n\nThe kernel looks good. Now let me create the Python wrapper."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":690,"cache_read_input_tokens":97180,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":690},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4866d367-d48b-4a34-81f5-869c2bcf590b","uuid":"d7ab08fc-6564-430d-b447-fdaea26d5b6e"}
